page.title: 14KINGSWOOD
page.content: To the north of the Danesholme estate,and to the west of the Kingswood estate there is an area of ancient woodland called{Kingswood. {Kingswood}was once part of{Rockingham {forest.}The wood was left when Corby was built,the wood was left on purpose. The wood is very useful as it is full of old trees such as oak,ash, hazel etc.There are also two ponds which have frogs and toads in them as well as insect nymphs and larvae. It is also possible if you look very carefully to find evidence that owls feed there during the nights (owl pellets). Kingswood is completely surrounded by houses.Children often play in rhe woods,although some parents will not let their children go there.
